                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1113/46: Telegram (part air)</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-03T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 3, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 4—5:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>287. Department’s 79, May 27, 7 p.m.<note n="98" xml:id="d416fn98">Not
                        printed.</note> Wiley reports from Vienna that Gestapo orally states four
                    S.A. men who attacked Heller served 14-day sentences and Orts group [<hi
                        rend="italic">Ortsgruppe</hi>] severely reprimanded. Written confirmation of
                    this has been promised by Gestapo here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
